gov.ca.water.calgui.results

Class DSSGrabber2

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.ca.water.calgui.results.DSSGrabber2

  • public class DSSGrabber2
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to grab (generate) DSS time series BASED ON DTS list for a set of scenarios passed in a JList. Each scenario is a string that corresponds to a fully qualified (?) DSS file name. The DSS_Grabber instance provides access to the following:
    • Main time series (result, including necessary math) for each scenario
    • Secondary series (control) where indicated for each scenario
    • Difference for main time series for each scenario
    • Exceedance for main time series for each scenario
    Typical usage sequence:
    • DSS_Grabber
    • setIsCFS
    • setBase
    • setLocation
    • setDateRange
    • getPrimarySeries
    • getSecondarySeries
    • Other calculations

      • setLocation

        public void setLocation(java.lang.String locationName)
        Sets dataset (DSS) names to read from scenario DSS files, title, and axis labels according to location specified using a coded string. The string is currently used as a lookup into either Schematic_DSS_Links4.table (if it starts with "SchVw") or into GUI_Links3.table. These tables may be combined in Phase 2.
        Parameters:
        string - index into GUI_Links3.table or Schematic_DSS_Link4.table

        public hec.io.TimeSeriesContainer[] getDifferenceSeries(hec.io.TimeSeriesContainer[] timeSeriesResults)
        Calculates the difference between scenarios and the base for a set of DSS results.
        Parameters:
        timeSeriesResults - array of HEC TimeSeriesContainer objects, each representing a set of results for a scenario. Base is in position [0].

        array of HEC TimeSeriesContainer objects (size one less than timeSeriesResult. Position [0] contains difference [1]-[0], position [1] contains difference [2]-[0], ...
